doc.previous: The Marshall Islands are threatened by the potential effects of sea level rise 32 According to the president of Nauru the Marshall Islands are the nation ranked as the most endangered due to flooding from climate change 33
doc.after: The islands have few natural resources and imports far exceed exports  In 2007 the Marshall Islands joined the International Labor Organization which means its labor laws will comply with international benchmarks This may impact business conditions in the islands 34
